  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To review the influence of patient derived PRGF on the healing process of Achilles tendon
      after a surgical correction of a complete tear.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Autologous platelet-rich matrices may aid in post surgical patients by promoting and
      accelerating tissue healing because of the release of growth factors including transforming
      growth factor (TGF)-beta1 and platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF) from platelet
      alpha-granules.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
